'''''Star Wars Insider'' 51''' is the fifty-first issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was the first issue published under the new direction of [[Wizards of the Coast]] and the last produced by former [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] president [[Dan Madsen]], who oversaw the creation of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' in [[1987]] under the title ''The Lucasfilm Fan Club Magazine''. It's also the last issue for longtime Editor-in-Chief [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]. Managing Editor [[Scott Chernoff]], who had been running the magazine, stayed on for a while but stepped back to Contributing Editor status after this issue.

Originally scheduled for an [[October]]/[[November]] [[2000]] release in accordance with the magazine's regular bimonthly publication schedule, issue 51 was delayed until [[January]] [[2001]] due to the change in publishers, and was only sent out to subscribers rather than also to newsstands.

==Contents==
*"[[Sir Alec Guinness: 1914-2000]]" {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*:<small>A fond look back at the life and work of one of the greatest actors of the 20th century.</small>
*"[[Harrison Ford: What Lies Ahead]]" {{C|by Jason Fry and [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>The star of ''Star Wars'', Indiana Jones, and ''What Lies Beneath'' talks about his recent performance as a bad guy and looks ahead to what his next project might be.</small>
*"[[Meet the New Stars of Episode II]]"
*:<small>Here are the new faces you'll be getting to know in the second episode of the ''Star Wars'' saga!</small>
*"[[Jonathan Hales: Inside the Screenplay to Episode II]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>Episode II co-screenwriter Jonathan Hales talks about writing for Young Indiana Jones on television, and Young Darth Vader in the newest chapter of the ''Star Wars'' prequel trilogy.</small>
*"[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Episode I|''Inside the Worlds of Episode I'']]"
*:<small>An exclusive look at an extraordinary new book exploring the environments of Episode I ''The Phantom Menace''.</small>
*"[[Christopher Lee: Rings of Fire]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>The star of Dracula, ''Lords of the Rings'', and now Episode II talks about his new ''Star Wars'' character, working with Peter Cushing, and the wizardry of Tolkien.</small>

